abstract: “Love doesn’t always happen how or when you think it will. This love was worth waiting for.”
snippet: “Love doesn’t always happen how or when you think it will. This love was worth waiting for.”
lead_paragraph: While growing up, Julia Mathis imagined having a fancy wedding with a huge crowd, a string of bridesmaids and a towering cake. Her mother had married her father at the age of 21 and that partnership held solid for 40 years.

abstract: Pressuring the Fed to juice the economy as he seeks re-election, the president is toying with an unprecedented challenge to its independence.
snippet: Pressuring the Fed to juice the economy as he seeks re-election, the president is toying with an unprecedented challenge to its independence.
lead_paragraph: President Trump has been attacking the Federal Reserve and its chairman, Jerome H. Powell, because he is angry that the central bank’s efforts to keep the economy healthy over the long term may dampen the stock market and economic growth in the short term just as he gears up for re-election.

abstract: The New England Patriots owner, who has been under legal scrutiny in a Florida prostitution case, accepted one of Israel’s most prestigious awards for his philanthropy there.
snippet: The New England Patriots owner, who has been under legal scrutiny in a Florida prostitution case, accepted one of Israel’s most prestigious awards for his philanthropy there.
lead_paragraph: After New England Patriots owner Robert K. Kraft was charged in February with soliciting prostitution, some of the many charities that he has supported wrestled with what to do.

lead_paragraph: Andrea Colon, an 18-year-old student activist from Far Rockaway, Queens, traveled a thousand miles to a presidential campaign stop for Mayor Bill de Blasio in Hiawatha, Iowa — not to hear his views on national issues, but to confront him about arrests in schools.

abstract: Expectations that the central bank would begin to cut interest rates this year have been fueling a stock market rally all month.
snippet: Expectations that the central bank would begin to cut interest rates this year have been fueling a stock market rally all month.
lead_paragraph: Stocks edged higher Wednesday, after the Federal Reserve indicated that a growing number of the central bank’s policymakers now expect to cut interest rates this year.
